In England, in the seven days to 05 September, there were 191,325 new confirmed cases (338.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 August, there were 171,908 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 11% (19,417 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 September is 6,155,149 (10,884.4 cases per 100,000 population).
